                "imgDesc": "<p>The Mother of Jinn, Liloupar, meets a shepherd, Ormazd.</p>",
                "key": "History of Gurabad"
              },
              {
                "id": "gallery_character25207",
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/10/07/237301566/f6bde2c42f527aa148fc9cd30be3da9e_4988327291725696841.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Liloupar gives powers to Ormazd.</p>",
                "key": "History of Gurabad"
              },
              {
                "id": "gallery_character4883",
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/10/07/237301566/b29fc1a36d65e169dac3248cda724ac3_4875078636755316057.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Huvashtra the Tyrant, who was overthrown by Ormazd.</p>",
                "key": "History of Gurabad"
              },
              {
                "id": "gallery_character84804",
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/10/07/237301566/2d5025fba5faf39468091f5603008220_6079564577116379689.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Reign of Ormazd.</p>",
                "key": "History of Gurabad"
              },
              {
                "id": "gallery_character33448",
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/10/07/237301566/5f8e7a81863a10b0bdd25202e06e4ba2_8616040967189503990.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>\"...I, Ormazd, was once a humble shepherd in the desert. 'Twas by King Deshret's grace that I could muster my forces and overthrow Huvashtra the Tyrant...\"</p><p>\"King Deshret sent the great Jinni from the City of the Moon Maiden to assist me in building Gurabad and in gathering the wandering tribes of the desert. Since then, the common folk and the powerful alike have led prosperous lives under King Deshret's guidance...\"</p><p>\"I hereby half dedicate my beloved kingdom, my trusted subjects, and my obedient slaves to my immortal partner, Liloupar, to be hers in perpetuity, and the other half, I submit to my lord, King Deshret.\"</p><p>\"When the time comes, I shall leave my kingdom and people behind — in white vestments I shall clad myself, as I offer a sacrifice of a thousand slaves...\"</p>",
                "key": "History of Gurabad"
              }
            ],
